&gt;Cayley&#39;s Formula: the number of trees on $n$ vertices is $n^{n-2}$

This formula is first discovered  in 1860, using determinants. With modern methods, we can not only solve this problem in a one paragraphs, but also count the number of trivalent trees with --&gt;
